I have brought along
no food and no water

18:23.367 --> 18:25.500
and no method
for signaling anyone,

18:25.500 --> 18:27.400
and my cell phone here
doesn't get any service.

18:27.400 --> 18:30.267
I am considering using one of
my shoelaces here

18:30.267 --> 18:32.133
as a fishing line

18:32.133 --> 18:35.167
and pieces of my wallet as bait.

18:35.167 --> 18:37.833
And I only pray that
I am rescued

18:37.833 --> 18:41.500
before that begins to seem like
a viable survival plan.

18:45.200 --> 18:47.700
Jesus Christ.

18:55.900 --> 18:58.367
Fish don't eat wallets.

18:58.367 --> 19:00.867
(Forrest voice-over)
My review of making a wish
come true

19:00.867 --> 19:03.500
had left me metaphorically
lost at sea.

19:03.500 --> 19:06.667
Being literally lost at sea
was even worse.

19:06.667 --> 19:09.200
There is a flashing red light
on the camera now,

19:09.200 --> 19:12.600
which I assume means that
the battery is running low.

19:12.600 --> 19:17.333
I would like to say something to
the love of my life,

19:17.333 --> 19:20.700
my--my ex-wife, Suzanne.

19:20.700 --> 19:23.933
Suzanne, I--

19:23.933 --> 19:26.067
I'm pretty sure
I'm gonna die out here.

19:26.067 --> 19:27.867
[static crackles]

19:27.867 --> 19:30.267
[laughs]

19:30.267 --> 19:32.067
Hello.

19:32.067 --> 19:35.667
I do not know how many days
I have been at sea.

19:35.667 --> 19:38.133
(Forrest voice-over)
I had been at sea for 96 days.

19:38.133 --> 19:40.233
It is difficult to look at
this footage now,

19:40.233 --> 19:42.467
but the mere fact of my survival

19:42.467 --> 19:44.867
is a beautiful,
glorious miracle.

19:44.867 --> 19:48.467
I've been swept into some kind
of a floating trash vortex

19:48.467 --> 19:50.267
in the middle of the ocean.

19:50.267 --> 19:53.133
I have been killing and eating
the sea birds

19:53.133 --> 19:55.467
that perch on top of
the garbage.

19:55.467 --> 19:58.167
I've been strangling them
and snapping their necks

19:58.167 --> 20:00.100
with my hands.

20:00.100 --> 20:01.700
And it's not a bad diet.

20:01.700 --> 20:04.933
One of the things that I have
been blessed to find here

20:04.933 --> 20:06.967
in this garbage island

20:06.967 --> 20:09.100
is a battery that works
in this camera

20:09.100 --> 20:10.967
so that I can continue
to talk to you

20:10.967 --> 20:14.400
because I have had important
experiences

20:14.400 --> 20:16.633
to share with you
about rowboats.

20:16.633 --> 20:18.867
They are--
[static crackles]

20:18.867 --> 20:21.233
Wow.

20:21.233 --> 20:23.967
You were lost at sea
for a long time.

20:23.967 --> 20:25.633
Yep.
[laughs]

20:25.633 --> 20:27.633
I want to thank anybody
who has ever contributed

20:27.633 --> 20:30.333
to the great Mid-Pacific
trash flotilla.

20:30.333 --> 20:32.900
If you don't properly dispose
of your garbage,

20:32.900 --> 20:35.133
you saved my life.

20:35.133 --> 20:37.433
I would also like to thank
the gruesome practice

20:37.433 --> 20:39.033
of illegal whale hunting.

20:39.033 --> 20:41.400
For it was a group of
renegade Japanese whalers

20:41.400 --> 20:44.800
who ultimately found me
and brought me to safety.

20:44.800 --> 20:48.267
Arigatou gozaimasu.

20:48.267 --> 20:51.067
Spending time
alone on a rowboat

20:51.067 --> 20:54.200
is a horrifying, desperate
struggle for survival

20:54.200 --> 20:57.767
that cuts a man off from
his life and his loved ones

20:57.767 --> 21:00.600
frequently causing him
to pray for death.

21:00.600 --> 21:02.367
Spending time on a rowboat,

21:02.367 --> 21:05.500
half a star.

21:14.533 --> 21:16.333
The ocean is a force of nature

21:16.333 --> 21:18.567
that must be taken seriously
at all times,

21:18.567 --> 21:20.733
and it's not something to
be trifled with

21:20.733 --> 21:23.467
or toyed with
or--or enjoyed for fun.

21:23.467 --> 21:27.133
I am sorry that
I disrespected the sea!
